This directory holds static OpenSSL libcrypto archives (one per Android
ABI) used by the SQLCipher codec in this fork of WatermelonDB. They are
built from official OpenSSL release tarballs by `scripts/vendor-openssl.sh`,
which pins a specific version and verifies its SHA-256.

OpenSSL is © The OpenSSL Project Authors. OpenSSL 3.x is licensed under
the Apache License 2.0, available at:
  https://github.com/openssl/openssl/blob/master/LICENSE.txt

The built archives are NOT committed to this repository. They are produced
on demand by `scripts/vendor-openssl.sh` (which runs automatically via the
`postinstall` npm hook when an Android NDK is available) and are included
in released dist tarballs. The pinned version is recorded in
`scripts/vendor-openssl.sh`.

Redistribution: when you publish an application built against this
directory you inherit the Apache 2.0 notice requirement. Reproduce the
OpenSSL license in your application's third-party-licenses page or about
screen.
